CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 1, 1958, pg. 11, reads: "Unionites Fete Dr. Proctor - Dr. Samuel D. Proctor, president of Virginia Union University, was the guest of the alumni and friends of the school at a dinner at the Greene Hearth, Jan. 27. At the guest table, left to right, are Mrs. James B. Cayce, Dr. J. A. Williams, Mrs. Homer S. Brown, the Rev. A. M. Waller, chairman; Dr. Proctor, Mrs. A. M. Waller, the Rev. James B. Cayce, vice president of the Baptist State Convention; Mrs. R. L. Vann, trustee of Virginia Union; the Rev. Charles H. Foggie and Judge Homer S. Brown of Common Pleas Court.  The Rev. H. H. Gaines served as chairman of the dinner. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Mrs. Cayce, Dr. J. A. Williams, Wilhelmina Byrd Brown, Rev. A. M. Waller, Virginia Union President Dr. Samuel D. Proctor, Mrs. Waller, Rev. James B. Cayce, Jessie Vann, Rev. Charles H. Foggie, and Judge Homer S. Brown, seated at banquet table for dinner in honor of Dr. Proctor, in Greene Hearth
